properties.areaDesc: Western Nevada Basin and Range including Pyramid Lake
properties.headline: Wind Advisory issued January 16 at 9:58AM PST until January 16 at 7:00PM PST by NWS Reno NV
properties.description:
* CHANGES...None.

* WHAT...South winds 20 to 30 mph with gusts up to 55 mph
expected. Gusts up to 45 mph on Pyramid Lake with wave heights
2 to 3 feet.

* WHERE...Western Nevada Basin and Range including Pyramid Lake.

* WHEN...From 7 AM this morning to 7 PM PST this evening.

* IMPACTS...Gusty winds could blow around unsecured objects.
Tree limbs could be blown down and a few power outages may
result.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Strong cross winds will occur along
Interstate 80 and U.S. Highway 50 with the strongest winds
after 11 AM. Areas of blowing dust may result in sudden
reductions to visibility.
properties.instruction:
Make sure loose outdoor items such as patio furniture and trash
cans are secured before winds increase. Make sure you have extra
food and water on hand, flashlights with spare batteries and/or
candles in the event of a power outage.

NWSheadline: WIND ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 7 PM PST THIS EVENING
